DETR

{% raw %} 
model = DETR(n_classes=dls.c, hidden_dim=256)
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
learn = Learner(dls, model, metrics=[accuracy], wd=0.1, splitter=detr_split).to_fp16()
learn.freeze()
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
learn.lr_find()

Train with attention

We will predict with an attention layer over the full output sequence from the LSTM layer.

{% raw %} 
model2 = ConvLSTM(num_classes=dls.c, hidden_dim=256, lstm_layers=2, bidirectional=True, attention=True)
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
learn2 = Learner(dls, model2, metrics=[accuracy], wd=0.1, cbs=[ModelResetter()], splitter=convlstm_splitter).to_fp16()
learn2.freeze()
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
learn2.lr_find()

SuggestedLRs(lr_min=0.002290867641568184, lr_steep=0.005248074419796467)
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
learn2.fit_one_cycle(10, 5e-3)
0.00% [0/10 00:00<00:00]
epoch train_loss valid_loss accuracy time

88.26% [263/298 00:47<00:06 2.0170]
